  <description type="morphology">Stems  creeping; scales brown, broadly lanceolate, margins entire.  Petiole  15--40(--50) cm.  Blade  oblong-lanceolate, 1-pinnate, 30--75 × 8--25 cm, ± narrowed to base with reduced proximal pinnae, broadest above base, abruptly acuminate to apex.  Pinnae  linear, ± entire to shallowly crenulate, base truncate or acroscopically auriculate, apex acuminate.  Veins  usually 1--2-forked, nearly reaching sinuses between crenations.  Sori  elongate, straight or slightly falcate, single or rarely double; indusia vaulted, ± thick. 2 n  = 80.</description>
  <description type="habitat">Moist woods and slopes in neutral soil</description>
